My review, changes in red...

http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#install-guide/config_block_storage.html
{quote}
Note: Storage SANs are deprecated as of Eucalyptus 4.4; to be removed in a future release. {color:red}The open source (free) backend providers will continue to be supported.{color}
...
...that can be attached {color:red}-by- to{color} a VM...  _(seems like a nit, but you attach a volume to a VM from either the console or the Euca CLI, not from within the running VM)_
{quote}

http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#install-guide/config_storage_ceph_rbd.html
{quote}
Verify that uploading snapshots to object storage are enabled:
_Maybe refer to, or summarize, the description of {{ZONE.storage.shouldtransfersnapshots}} in http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#euca2ools-guide/euca-properties.html ?_
...
Set the maximum number of deltas {color:red}created before creating a new full snapshot:{color}
_Maybe refer to, or summarize, the description of {{ZONE.storage.maxsnapshotdeltas}} in http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#euca2ools-guide/euca-properties.html ?_
{quote}

http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#euca2ools-guide/euca-properties.html
{quote}
{{ZONE.storage.maxsnapshotdeltas}}
Add: 
{color:red}Currently, snapshot deltas are only used when your backend is Ceph-RBD. 
You must set {{ZONE.storage.shouldtransfersnapshots}} to true, to enable snapshot deltas.
{color}
...
{{ZONE.storage.shouldtransfersnapshots}}
Enable snapshot transfer to the OSG. Default is true. {color:red}Setting it to {{false}} will disable storing snapshots (full or delta) in object storage. While a {{false}} setting will reduce object storage requirements, it also prevents the ability to use a snapshot from one availability zone to create a volume in another zone. You can still take and use snapshots even if this is false, but you can only use a snapshot to create a volume in the same zone. Must be set to {{true}} to use snapshot deltas, which are managed by setting the {{ZONE.storage.maxsnapshotdeltas}} property.{color}
{quote}

http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#admin-guide/ops_ts_snapshot_fail.html
_As currently written, this section only applies to DAS and Overlay. We could clarify and generalize it, and add notes about snap deltas:_
{quote}
{color:red}On the SC, depending on the back end used for storage:
* For Overlay, use the {{df}} command to check the disk space in {{/var/lib/eucalyptus/volumes}}.
* For DAS, use the {{lvdisplay}} command to check the disk space in the DAS volumes.
* For any other back end, use its specific commands to check the free space for storage allocated for volumes.
{color}
Is there enough space?

    Yes:
{color:red}On the OSG host, depending on the back end used for object storage:
* For Walrus, use the {{df}} command to check the disk space in {{/var/lib/eucalyptus/bukkits}}. 
* For RiakCS or Ceph-RGW, use its specific commands to check the free space for storage allocated for buckets and objects.
{color}
Is there enough space?
        Yes.
            Use euserv-describe-services and note the IP addresses for the OSG and SC.
            SSH to SC and ping the OSG.

            Are there error messages?
                Yes:

                Check the SC and the OSG logs for the snapshot ID.
                No:

                Check the network connection between the SC and the OSG.
        No:
        Delete volumes or add disk space.
    No:
    Delete volumes or add disk space.
{quote}

http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#install-guide/config_storage_ceph_rbd_hyperviser.html
{quote}
_(A bit off-topic but noticed while reviewing)_
5. {color:red}If you are NOT using the RHEV package procedure to install the qemu-kvm-rhev and qemu-img-rhev packages, i{color}nstall Eucalyptus-built RHEV packages:
{quote}

I just discovered that the names in the qemu packages have changed for RHEL7/CentOS7 (regardless of whether you get them from the RHEV subscription or the Eucalyptus repo), so change all the qemu-kvm-rhev and qemu-img-rhev references to qemu-kvm-ev and qemu-img-ev in http://builds.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/branch/master/#install-guide/config_storage_ceph_rbd_hyperviser.html . 

Furthermore, I've discovered the 'yum install' step's description is still not quite right. Correcting myself, please change it to something like:

{quote}
Install the RHEV packages {{qemu-kvm-rhev}} and {{qemu-img-rhev}}. The {{yum}} command will find them either in your RHEV subscription or the Eucalyptus repository, based on your preparation in the previous step.
{quote}
